> > and calculation of addresses to be made and then stored to the 
> > blitter registers even before the blit is started.
> 
>     Not too much :) 4 registers to init, it takes virtually nothing :)

Not the way Blitz does it:

For the first plane

4 channel pointers (Blitz always uses all 4 channels)
4 channel modulos
first word and last word mask registers
BLTCON0 & 1 registers
BLTSIZE register

And for subsequent planes
3 channel pointers (for cookiecut, and 2xdestination plane)
BLTSIZE register


