Sorry, it's up to you.  The hardware will only tell you if your sprite has
hit a pixel of the given colour, nothing more...

> What is
> HANDLE by the way? =)

It is the offset of your shape or sprite that is actually put on the x,y
location you have moved it to.

So, if you have set the handle (you use the "Handle" command for this) of a
16 x 16 shape to 8,8 and Blit it at 100,100 on a bitmap, the top left
corner of the shape will be at 92,92 on the Bitmap, and the center will be
at 100,100

If you have set the handle at 0,0  (the default) and Blit it at 100,100 now
the top left corner will be at 100,100


But, I don't think you can alter the handle of a Sprite once it has been
created... 

