Check the cordinate of your sprite and compare it to the center of
rectangle. ie if y is lower than rectangle center y then it,s on lower half
and then test the x with same way. You can use hotspot or just make the
comparison point so that it takes account the fact that sprite coordinates
are for the topleft corner of the sprite image.

This of course can't tell you if the (round shaped?) sprite have hitted the
corner, and in which angle it did that. But it's fast and the bit testing
is left to the hardware, which is the most time consuming part.

