You have new types down pat...padding and all...the problem is when you
declare the new type...you made it a pointer to a variable, not a variable,
so what happens is that your newtype is never pointed at any memory address
for the variable

adding

*hello=allocmem(sizeof(test),$10000)

after the deftype points the varible *hello at the allocated memory

or you could just use

deftype .test hello

to make a standard variable (ie allocates the memory on the variable stack)
and remove all the stars from the code and access it like

hello\something=24

