@NODE "Mail_117" " RE: Foundation Intro (how?) "
From: Burkey <burkey@bigfoot.com>
Date: 02-18-00 17:20:55
Subject: @{b}RE: Foundation Intro (how?)@{ub}

> I was just playing Foundation, the other day, and I was
> wondering what teqniques Paul Burkey used, to play the
> intro directly from the CD, while the animation was
> playing?

yes.. I know! :)

It was a custom anim format. It took each frame of the
animation and removed all of the pixels that hadn't
changed from the previous frame and also pixels that
were very close in appearance to the previous frame.
This explains why there is high and low quality versions
of the anim. One was very strict about how 'close' the
pixels had to be and the other was more relaxed about
it which meant more detail was lost. Then the data was
converted to 'delta' information meaning the pixels
were not stored as palette values but logical OR/AND
values that could be merged quite fast/easily with the
previous frame. This meant the pixels that had not
changed since the last frame would be full of Zero's
and would be easy to compress. The next stage was to
compress the information using custom compression code
written especially for the game by a 3rd party. The
compression was based on the Imploder algorithm which
gave very fast depack times. The fact that the anim
format uses 3rd party compression explains why I've
not been able to release the actual animation code
(The same compression was used for all of Foundations
data files.) Each frames packed data was then dumped
out to a file. The rest of the anim format was quite
simple, just one palette was used for the whole anim
which wasn't so good, but allowed me to use a fade
in/out technique and also helped to reduce file size
because of the colour limitation.

Playback was of the anim was fairly simple, just load
the packed section, unpack, merge to previous frame
using basic AND/OR logic (a few lines of Asm code) and
display. I always planned to do this in a background
thread to make loading and unpacking asynchronous but
never found the inspiration to implement that in Blitz.

I hope that helps to answer your question!

Cheers,

Paul


@ENDNODE

