Make sure you are not trying to free a bitmap which you 
grabbed/borrowed/stole from a screen. I can't remember if Blitz tries 
to free it twice, or its possibly trying to free the planes 
separately, which they won't be on your Spectrum.

> 2.   More worrying, I get an "Unable to open screen" when I try to
> open a Spectrum screen using the Blitz Screen command.   Is there
> something special I should be doing?   Basically, I'm opening the
> screen with a screen mode of $40420001 which means nothing to me, but
> it is the only odd-looking thing there.   Any thoughts please?

Make sure you have the modes set up correctly in whatever prefs 
program for the card (i.e. Picasso96Mode prefs prog or whatever for 
CGFX). If you have not got $40420001 defined, then it won't be 
recognised as a valid screenmode.


