I'm not very keen to do any further coding, but I understand how great
it would be if things would run even faster than they do. If I had an
060/50 I think I would really be smokin cus the idea of double the
amount of graphics power that I have on my 040/25 is really quite
appealing for some great parallax and extra bobs and special effects
and so on. I also wish that there wasn't the overhead of having to
dump the fastram buffer into graphics card or chipmem cus that on its
own usually takes up about half the cpu time. I have tried of course
to render directly over the the bus into video ram but that turned out
even slower. Mind you a zorro3 card might have some advantage there.

Technology technology technology. You know, Dafel:Bloodline which is
done in blitz using Mildred, runs at 25fps on an 030/50. Uses Mildred
for the scrolling, tile engine, queues and bobs. Basically all the
graphics work, and with the game code running as well. So that's not a
bad achievement. It would be great though if there was even more cpu
time to spare on an 030.

I started trying to make a llamatron clone. It's a simple blank
background with bobs on top and it can achieve quite a number at a
nice speed, but on an 040, and I am still left wishing for more. And
why are 060's so much more expensive? Grr. 

Having been away from things for a while I have wondered if I might
suddenly see it all in a new light and come up with a radical way to
improve the speed, but all I can think of it to make a c2p/gfx-card
rendering system that only copies over the areas of the screen which
have changed.. tho its no use doing seperate c2p's for every bob drawn
cus when bobs overlap it will be less efficient and wanting to have
MORE bobs means that it would probably turn out to be faster to just
copy the whole lot. It's also harder to do scrolling when you aren't
c2p'ing the entire buffer, and slower - cus using hardware scrolling
means the bitmap has to be wider hense more c2p time, doh. lol

If only fastram were as fast as it is and were /displayable/ things
would be great. There's not much chance of the c2p/copy getting faster
either. Working in 256 colours does have a certain disadvantage. I
discovered that as I was thinking of doing a T-Zer0 beater ... which
might boast lots of colours but doesn't necessarily use all of the
bitplanes for each object. Some spaceships might only be 4 or 8
colours. So 8-bit graphics is at a slight disadvantage in that way.

Hmm... if only the masking could be faster and not need all that
memory access. It'd be great if the cpu had some more registers spare
too.

lol


