You can use semaphores to partially get around the reentrancy problem. 
In my GoldED plugin, I use a hash table for storing all the commands
that need to be highlighted, and I use semaphores to make sure that
while someone is using the table, that it can't be deleted or modified. 
You can set the semaphores up in the library init code, and then when
you want to use them it is just a simple OS call.

