What MUICycle does when used with an array is take the base of a
string array (pointer to pointers) and read each longword along the
array until 0, inserting the pointed to strings into the cycle..
For this reason, blitz linked lists cannot be used because the
pointers arn`t next to each other, they could be anywhere..

Try this:

  ; Enter 0-9 into a cycle gadget.
  ;
  NEWTYPE.arry
	a.s[11]
  End NEWTYPE
  DEFTYPE.arry c
  *cptr.b=&c
  For n.l=0 To 9
	c\a[n]=Chr$(n+48)
  Next
  MUICycle #MUI_Cycle,*cptr

; This should work fine..

