Well quite simple (don't know if those ecs sprites can be 64 pixels wide,
but AGA ones certainly can.)

So if we can use 5 sprites we can make 320 pixel wide 3+1 color "screen",
which can be as a playfield in front of or partially in front of bitplanes.

So take "blitz user manual" the white one which have those updated commands
and the is some of those bplconx registers, which have the sprite width
bits. so now you can make the sprites 64 bit wide and as high as your
display is. Then you will need to lay those sprites side by side so that
it will form a 320 pixel wide plane. The updation of the GFX on the sprites
is much more dificult than the bitmap GFX, so you need to write your own
asm routine for that. Or if it's static then it will be a lot easier.

from the registers you can also found a controlling register, which controls
how the bitplanes are shown or hidden under the sprite non transparent
colors. You can easily change this with a couple of cop instructiions.

First a wait for end of the last line you want to use the initial settings
then change the priorities.

