@NODE "Mail_357" " Re: Trail Hit Detection "
From: Paul <paulwest@stationone.demon.co.uk>
Date: 02-27-00 16:47:52
Subject: @{b}Re: Trail Hit Detection@{ub}

> What would be the best way to detect if a player in a Tron type game collided
> with the other players trail if it was made of blitted shapes? I don't want
> to have to keep coordinates for every bit of trail that has been left and I
> would like a method that isn't Blitz specific so I can use Mildred later if I
> want to. 

Are the tron cycles always going to move at 90 degree angles and the
bobs be plotted at even intervals? If so you could use one pixel in
the bob of a particular colour and use MPoint to check? Or just use
colours in the bobs that aren't used elsewhere and check using MPoint
too?

Use a stencil. This will work in blitz and Mildred. When you render
the trails using a stencil blit to render the trail to the stencil
(also). Then you can check against the stencil for collisions?

Or, use a second bitmap, hidden, on which you render things in
`colour', blocks of colour rather than images, so you can check who
owns what part of the trail?

